7_9	0.076557316	``Now it is trying to construct a system to allow small farmers to help them survive, to help them flourish.
7_10	0.059999037	It is also a turning point in its relationship to consumers.
7_11	0.068275824	The agency has never before been responsive to consumers' desires or demands''.
7_12	0.10229738	In an interview, Agriculture Secretary Dan Glickman said that if the public thought the standards were too strict they should let the department know during the 90-day comment period before the agency enacts the final rules.
7_13	0.084696522	``I'd rather go from too strict standards and ease them than going the other way,'' Glickman said.
7_14	0.12853308	The agency is clearly moving towards stricter definitions of what constitutes organic food.
7_15	0.13425164	After initially ignoring many of the recommendations of the National Organic Standards Board, which had been set up to help the agency formulate the regulations, the Agriculture Department has now taken all of the board's advice, including total prohibition of antibiotics in animals raised as organic; the use of 100 percent organic feed; and the requirement of outdoor access for animals.
